  "prompt": "How can I recover deleted photos from app lock new version?",
  "response": "Recovering deleted photos from an app that uses a lock or privacy feature can depend on a few factors, such as the specific app you're using and whether the photos were backed up elsewhere. Here are some general steps you can follow to try to recover deleted photos:\n\n1. **Check the App's Recently Deleted Folder**: Some photo apps have a \"Recently Deleted\" folder where deleted photos are temporarily stored before being permanently removed. Open the app and look for this feature.\n\n2. **Use Cloud Backups**: If the app was syncing with a cloud service (like Google Photos, iCloud, OneDrive), check those accounts to see if the deleted photos are stored there.\n\n3. **File Recovery Apps**: If the photos were stored on your device and deleted, you may be able to use a file recovery app to try and recover them. There are many third-party apps available for both Android and iOS.\n\n4. **Check Your Device's Gallery or Photos App**: Sometimes, deleted photos can be found in the default gallery or photos app, especially if they were imported or synced from another source.\n\n5. **Restore from Backup**: If you regularly back up your device, consider restoring it to a previous backup that may contain the deleted photos. Be cautious with this option, as it will overwrite any data that has been added since the backup was made.\n\n6. **Contact the App's Support**: If you're having trouble and the photos are vital, consider reaching out to the app\u2019s customer support for assistance.\n\nRemember to act quickly because the longer you wait, the more likely the deleted files may be overwritten, making recovery more difficult.",
